# Read the dataset

Data <- read.csv(file = "Average_Annual_Wages_by_Degree_Utah_2012.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
Data$Average.Annual.Wages.2012 <- as.numeric(gsub(",", "", Data$Average.Annual.Wages.2012))

Visualization 1

ggplot(Data, aes(x = `Award.Level`, y = `Average.Annual.Wages.2012`)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "brown") +
  labs(title = "Average Annual Wages by Award Level in Utah (2012)",
       x = "Award Level",
       y = "Average Annual Wage") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

Visualization 2

Data$Enrolled.in.2011.12 <- as.numeric(gsub(",", "", Data$Enrolled.in.2011.12))
Data$Employed.in.2012 <- as.numeric(gsub(",", "", Data$Employed.in.2012))

Data_long <- gather(Data, key = "variable", value = "value", Enrolled.in.2011.12, Employed.in.2012)

ggplot(Data_long, aes(x = `Award.Level`, y = value, fill = variable)) +
  geom_bar(position = "dodge", stat = "identity") +
  labs(title = "Comparison of Enrolled and Employed Individuals by Award Level",
       x = "Award Level",
       y = "Count") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("Enrolled.in.2011.12" = "orange", "Employed.in.2012" = "lightblue"))
